 Leading soft drinks bottling company, Pepsi, will refresh the second edition of the DStv Premium Golf Day with a top-tier music ensemble, Storm Band, and crack disc jockey, DJ Xclusive (Rotimi Alakija). On Saturday, the DStv Premium Golf Day will be held at the Ikeja Golf Club, Lagos, according to a statement on Wednesday by Flykite Productions, organisers of the event. The statement described Storm Band as Nigeria’s “finest and fastest-growing” band, adding that DJ Xclusive has a global appeal, performing with American stars like Ne-Yo, Rihanna, Mario Winans, Brick and Lace, Nas and Fat Joe. Segun Ogunleye, General Manager, Marketing (Beverages), Seven-Up Bottling Company, Pepsi’s parent company, described Pepsi’s support for the DStv Premium Golf Day as an extension of its contribution to sports and entertainment in Nigeria. “Pepsi is proud to partner with DStv on the DStv Premium Golf Day and happy to refresh the many golfers participating in the competition,” Ogunleye said. Over 100 golfers from clubs across the country, to be chosen from about 600 registrants, will feature at the event, play with four clubs and a putter. Winners will emerge via a stroke play format. According to the statement, the event’s star prize is a business class flight ticket to Dubai for a weekend stay at a five-star hotel. The second prize is a business class ticket to Kigali, Rwanda, for a weekend stay at a five-star hotel, while the third prize is a weekend stay at a five-star hotel in Lagos. At the maiden edition in 2020, Dr. Ogunbiyi Ogunbanjo of Ikeja Golf Club, Messrs. Remi Olukoya and Rasheed Adebisi won the first, second and third prizes, respectively.